				\begin{document}$$E_{e/h}$$\end{document}. Hence, the energy of the simulated electrons Ei after propagation through the specimen needs to be taken into account. The normalized STEM intensity obtained by MC simulations can then be calculated according to Eq. (3).3II0=∑iEi-EcutoffEe/hNoE0-EcutoffEe/h\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
